        </p>
    </statement>
    
</question>

<p>
    Rules like <m>a + 1 = a</m> sound impossible, until we consider the strange
    creature we call <m>\infty</m>.
</p>

<subsection xml:id="subsec-infpredicatble">
    <title>Not always unpredictable</title>

    <p>
        However, <m>\infty</m> is not completely unpredictable in all cases. Actually, we should
        say that a pattern trending towards infinity is sometimes predictable.
    </p>

    <p>
        For example, consider the function <m>f(x) = \dfrac{1}{x^2}</m>. What happens as the variable <m>x</m> 
        gets larger and larger (trends towards <m>\infty</m>).
